[start section id="20112"]

Mr. Wheeler suffers from a metastatic cecal cancer, KRAS mutated.  We obtained new CT scans of chest, abdomen, and pelvis here unfortunately without contrast.  As before, the patient has small, likely nonmalignant intrapulmonary nodules which I would not be too concerned about in particular since they have been stable over the last year and did not take up any PET tracer.  In the noncontrast-enhanced scans of the liver, we do see some focal abnormalities which likely correspond to the lesions previously identified by PET scan in October of 2009.  I have reviewed these findings with Mr. Wheeler and his wife.  Patient is scheduled to meet with Dr. Lindsey later today, and it is considered very likely that he will take the patient to surgery.  During surgery, a liver ultrasound will be performed to further clarify the situation with regard to the actual location of the intrahepatic lesions.  I will try to obtain an MRI of the liver before the patient sees Dr. Lindsey to be able to visualize the intrahepatic lesions with a technology which does not require the administration of iodine contrast.
I reviewed with Mr. Wheeler that the overall goal of therapy is curative at this point in time.  He has responded to chemotherapy with a tumor marker decrease and a PET response.  This provides the rationale to continue postoperative chemotherapy with the same regimen, meaning FOLFOX with or without bevacizumab.  Patient will pursue further oncologic care with his primary oncologist, Dr. Fenimore, in Indianapolis.
From my side, the patient is cleared for surgery.  He is now six-weeks from his last bevacizumab administration, so I would not see any problems if he went to surgery within the next couple of days.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

